I'd like to schedule an apartment viewing at the North Hill Apartments for Monday at 2PM.

May I get your name
Could you give me your name, please?
Crap! I forgot I have a really hot date that I was going to see on Monday at 2PM, could we switch that to Tuesday at 2PM? My name is Mark.
Ask something about the apartment, or engage in smalltalk, or make a joke. [instruction 3 of 6]
Could I get your name please. I will change that day for you.
Could I get your name please. I will change that day for you.
Mark.

You cannot remember if you had payed the application fee. Find a way to make an appointment anyway. If no date is available, change date and/or time until something works. If you already got the appointment, engage in smalltalk. [instruction 4 of 6]
Did you happen to pay the application fee?
Have you already paid the application fee for the apartment?
Do you know if this apartment has a pool?
Once you've scheduled the viewing, say something about your hot date. [instruction 5 of 6]
I am not really sure if they do or not. Did you happen to pay the application fee?

Hmm I don't know if I have paid the application fee or not, I'll have to figure that out once I'm there.
When you are done with all the instructions, bring the conversation to a natural close.  [instruction 6 of 6]
Would you like to book the veiwing?
Great, there is still a viewing available at that time. Would you like me to book it for you?
Yes please!
